  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = Blue Gem.png\n|image = Blue Gem Dropped.png\n|foodType =[[Elemental]] [[File:Elemental.png|32px|link=Elemental]]<br>(non-survivor food)\n|hpRestored = 10\n|hungerRestored = 5\n|sanityRestored = 0\n|name = Blue Gem\n|droppedBy = {{Pic32|Grave}} {{pic32|Hound Mound/DST}} {{Pic32|Stalagmite}} {{Pic32|Ornate Chest}} {{Pic32|Ancient Pseudoscience Station}} {{Pic24|Ancient Statue}} {{Pic32|Sunken Chest}} {{Pic32|Geode Fruit}} {{pic24|Blue Gem Deer}} {{Pic32|Dragonfly}} {{Pic32|Malbatross}} {{Pic32|Great Depths Worm}} {{pic32|JIMBO}} {{pic24|Winter's Feast Tree}}<br>{{Pic32|Blue Hound}} (20%)<br>{{Pic32|Tumbleweed}} (0.04%)<br>{{pic24|Hot Spring Glass|Hot Spring}} (10%)<br>[[Earthquake]] (5%)\n|stack = 40\n|spawnCode = \"bluegem\"\n|crafting_infobox=\n<tabber>\nWandering Trader=\n{{Craft Infobox\n|craft_desctiption =''Bears the color of blue.''\n|crafting_text = {{Pic32|Pig Skin}}x3 \n|tier_text = {{Pic32|Wandering Trader}}\n|filter      = {{Pic32|Trading Filter}}\n}}\n|-|\nWilson=\n{{Craft Infobox\n|ingredient1 = Red Gem\n|multiplier1 = 2 ({{Pic|28|Wilson Portrait|Wilson}} only)\n|filter = {{Pic32|Wilson Filter}}\n|skill = Transmute Gems I\n|craft_desctiption = ''Transmute Red Gems into Blue Gems.''\n|skillOwner = Wilson}}\n</tabber>\n\n\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = It sparkles with cold energy.\n|willow = Ugh. This one is ugly.\n|wolfgang = Pretty rock.\n|wendy = Blue like... er... a sad bird?\n|wx78 = IT IS SLIGHTLY COLD\n|wickerbottom = It is cold.\n|woodie = It's very cold.\n|maxwell = Blue brings ice.\n|wagstaff = Its geometrical shape concentrates endothermic energy.\n|wigfrid = An icy blue sapphire.\n|webber = Glittering and cool.\n|walani = The color of the ocean!\n|warly = Such a cool blue.\n|woodlegs = It gleams true blue!\n|wilba = ALL THAT GLITTERS 'TIS COLD\n|wormwood = Cold shiny\n|wheeler = Ohh. Sparkly. I like sparkly.\n|winona = It's a gem. A gem that's blue.\n|wortox = Somber blue from seabeds grew.\n|wurt = Pretty rock.\n|walter = A magic blue gem!\n|wanda = Why do people say things are as blue as the sea? The sea isn't very blue at all!\n|choose = wilson}}\nThe '''Blue Gem''' is an item used to craft several [[Magic]]al Items. It can be used to craft the [[Ice Staff]], [[Chilled Amulet]] and [[Purple Gem]].\n\nBlue Gems can be used to turn [[Chester]] into [[Snow Chester]] by placing at least one in each of his inventory slots on a [[Full Moon]], granting him slower food spoilage like a mobile [[Ice Box]]. \n\nBlue Gems can be used to craft a [[Salt Box]] and inserted into [[Cratered Moonrock]]s to acquire a Blue [[Moonlens]]. They can also be used to power [[Winona's G.E.M.erator]].\n\n== Gathering ==\n* [[Dragonfly]] and the [[Malbatross]] drop Blue Gems upon death. \n* Blue [[Gem Deer]] will also drop a Blue Gem if killed or if Klaus is dead.\n* Blue Gems have a 0.04% chance to be dropped by [[Tumbleweed]]s.\n* [[Sunken Chest]]s can contain a Blue Gem, with equal chance of a [[Red Gem]] in its place.\n* Blue Gems can be crafted by Wilson if he has obtained \"[[Transmute Gems I]]\".\n* 15% chance to be found in [[Ornate Chest]]\n\n=={{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Red Gem\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|result = Purple Gem}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Spear\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|result = Ice Staff}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Gold Nugget\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|result = Chilled Amulet|item3=Gold Nugget|item4=Gold Nugget}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|count1 = 1\n|item3 = Salt Crystals\n|count3 = 10\n|item2 = Cut Stone\n|count2 = 1\n|result = Salt Box\n|tool = Alchemy Engine}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Cratered Moonrock\n|result = Blue Moonlens\n|note = Obtained by inserting the Gem into the Cratered Moonrock.}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Thulecite\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Twigs\n|count3 = 1\n|result = Icebell\n|character = Wolfgang\n|skill = Dumbbell Developer}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Bio Data\n|count2 = 4\n|tool = Bio Scanalyzer\n|result = Refrigerant Circuit\n|character = WX-78}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Moon Rock\n|result = Freeze Rounds\n|resultcount = 20\n|tool = Prestihatitator\n|character = Walter\n}}{{Recipe|item1=Blue Gem|item2=Thulecite|count2=2|item3=Nightmare Fuel|count3=2|item4=Red Gem|result=Thulecite Slingshot Frame|character=Walter|skill=Advanced Frames}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|item2 = Blue Gem\n|result = Red Gem\n|character = Wilson\n|skill = Transmute Gems I}}\n{{Recipe\n|item6 = Yellow Gem\n|item2 = Orange Gem\n|item3 = Green Gem\n|item4 = Purple Gem\n|item5 = Red Gem\n|item1 = Blue Gem\n|result = Iridescent Gem\n|character = Wilson\n|skill = Transmute Gems III}}\n\n== {{pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia==\n* Blue Gems were introduced in the ''A Winter's Tale'' update.\n* Blue Gems used to have the same shape as Red Gems.\n* The old Blue Gem appearance can be seen on the Ultimate Survival Inventory poster sold on Klei's official merch store.\n\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nBlue Gem emoji from official Klei Discord server.png|Medal blue emoji from official Klei Discord server.\nFile:Bluegem HD.png|The new high-resolution texture.\nCD bluegem.png|Original HD icon from Bonus Materials from [[CD Don't Starve]].\nBlue Gem 128x128.png|Icon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\n</gallery>\n<br /><tabber>\nResources=\n{{Resources}}\n|-|\nCraftable Items=\n{{Craftable Items and Structures on DST}}\n|-|\nFood=\n{{Food}}\n</tabber>\n[[vi: Ngọc Lam]]\n[[Category:Naturally Spawning Objects]]\n[[Category:Gems]]\n[[Category:Resources]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[Category:Minerals]]\n[[Category:Boss Dropped Items]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]"
}
